What you need to know:

The British boxer will be in action for the first time since he outpointed Andy Ruiz Jr in Saudi Arabia to regain the WBA, WBO and IBF belts he lost to the same opponent at Madison Square Garden in June 2019They will finally go toe-to-toe in front of 1,000 spectators at Wembley ArenaThe Briton said he was ready to take punches and go all 12 rounds if needed to ensure he took his record to 24-1 on Saturday